Creating a Debian Package with Checkinstall

First, you'll need to install the checkinstall tool (if not already installed). 

You can do this by running the following command in your terminal:

sudo apt-get install checkinstall

Then, run the following command from your project directory:

chmod +x install.sh

sudo checkinstall --pkgname=framenux-radio --pkgversion=1.0.0 --maintainer=maintainer@example.com --deldoc=yes --delspec=yes --backup=no --requires="python3, python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0" --install=yes ./install.sh


